epos/sktime/sktime/labels/module:forecasting","name":"module:forecasting","color":"35FCCE","default":false,"description":""},{"id":3796180314,"node_id":"LA_kwDOCVKAsc7iRR1a","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/labels/enhancement","name":"enhancement","color":"fef2c0","default":true,"description":"Adding new functionality"}],"state":"open","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":0,"created_at":"2022-04-07T09:45:41Z","updated_at":"2022-04-07T09:47:43Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"COLLABORATOR","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"We are, or soon will, be interfacing two resp three implementations of SARIMAX and auto-SARIMAX:\r\n\r\n* `pmdarima` ARIMA and AutoARIMA\r\n* `statsmodels` SARIMAX\r\n* `statsforecast` (Auto)ARIMA\r\n\r\n(and imo it makes a lot of sense to have multiple, e.g., to allow scientific comparison or selection over implementation)\r\n\r\nQuestions:\r\n* how do we name algorithms?\r\n* how do we name modules?\r\n* should there be one backend-independent \"dispatcher\"?\r\n* we need to document ARIMA vs SARIMAX better, imo, see the point of confusion below\r\n\r\nI also want to point out a frequent point of confusion:\r\neven though some of these models may be called only \"ARIMA\", i.e., without \"S\" and \"X\", they in fact all allow specification of seasonal components and exogeneous data, which would make the correct full designation of all three interfaced models \"SARIMAX\" or \"Auto-SARIMAX\".\r\n\"ARIMA\" is the more widely known designation for the model class, so from a user recognition perspective it may be preferable to offer these under the label \"ARIMA\", while explaining in the docstring that it includes SARIMAX.","closed_by":null,"reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/issues/2402/reactions","total_count":1,"+1":1,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/sktime/sktime/issues/2402/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null}